rComments: Overall, I enjoyed her class! It can be difficult to take notes because she speaks quickly and the majority of the information is not on the slides but she is always willing to repeat any information you may have missed. She gives great hints on what will be on the midterms and final. You have options (reflections or term paper) which is great!

It was her second time teaching this class and I think she did a great job! She wants her students to pass and I really enjoyed her 7-10 classes. She's also a history teacher, so get ready to write a lot of notes. She gives you the chance to write reflections every 2 weeks to raise your grade or do a final paper. Good prof overall!

I liked the course content but sometimes I couldn't see a straight line in her teaching. To be fair, she taught this class for the first time. Provides slides that are not very useful, talks quite fast which makes it hard to take adequate notes. Four reflections (4x5%), paper+template (30%+10%), final (40%). Good prepping for the final.

Prof. Thivierge tried her best to make the class interesting but at times was difficult to follow. Doesn't put most of the material on the slides to make sure you show up to class. Reflections in lieu of a midterm, but ridiculously difficultly graded. Paper was long but not too difficult. Final was extremely easy!
